title: Library of the World's Best Mystery and Detective Stories 6 Vols
description:
Library of the World's Best Mystery and Detective Stories in 6 Vols

by Julian Hawthorne

Published in 1908 by The Review of Reviews Company

Vol. 1. American: J. Hawthorne, F.M. Crawford, M.E.W. Freeman, M.D. Post, A. Bierce, 

E.A. Poe, W. Irving, C.B. Brown

Vol. 2. English-Scotch: R. Kipling, E. Castle, R.L. Stevenson, A.C. Doyle, S. 

Weyman, W. Collins, and others

Vol. 3. English-Irish: F. O'Brien, Bulwer-Lytton, T. De Quincey, C.R. Maturin, L. 

Sterne, W.M. Thackeray, and others

Vol. 4. French-Italian-Spanish-Latin: Maupassant, Mille, Adam, erckmann-Chatrian, 

Balzac, Voltaire, Alarcon, Capuana, Apulcius, Pliny, the Younger.

Vol. 5. German-Russian-Scandinavian: G. Meyrink, P. Heyse, F. Hoffman,

v. Krestovski, O. Larssen, D. Theden, W. Hauff, A. Chekhoff, J. Bergsoe, B. 

Ingermann, S.S. Blicher

Vol. 6. Oriental: Arabic, Japanese, Persian, Turkish, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Chinese. 

True stories of modern magic: A conjurer's confessions, Fraudulent spiritualism 

unveiled
